<content>
    <chapter line="1">Nāyaka kaṇḍa</chapter>
    <hangnum line="2" number="276"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="3"> Anāyakā <pageBreak edition="Myanmar" number="0.0165" /> vinassanti, nassanti bahunāyakā;</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="4">Thīnāyakā vinassanti, nassanti susunāyakā.</gathalast>
    <hangnum line="5" number="277"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="6"> Gavaṃ <pageBreak edition="Myanmar" number="0.0166" /> ce taramānānaṃ, ujuṃ gacchati puṅgavo;</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="7">Sabbā gāvī ujuṃ yanti, nette ujuṃ gate sati.</gathalast>
    <hangnum line="8" number="278"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="9"> Evameva manussesu, yo hoti seṭṭhasammato;</gatha1>
    <gatha2 line="10">So sace dhammaṃ carati, pageva itarā pajā.</gatha2>
    <gatha1 line="11">Gavaṃ ce taramānānaṃ, ujuṃ gacchati puṅgavo;</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="12">Sabbā gāvī ujuṃyanti, nette ujuṃ gate sati.</gathalast>
    <gatha1 line="13">Evameva <pageBreak edition="Myanmar" number="0.0167" /> manussesu, yo hoti seṭṭhasammato;</gatha1>
    <gatha2 line="14">So sace dhammaṃ carati, pageva itarā pajā;</gatha2>
    <gathalast line="15">Sabbaṃ raṭṭhaṃ sukhaṃ seti, rājā ce hoti dhammiko.</gathalast>
    <hangnum line="16" number="279"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="17"> Nodayāha vināsāya, bahunāyakatā bhusaṃ;</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="18">Milāyanti vinassanti, padmānyakkehi sattahi.</gathalast>
    <hangnum line="19" number="280"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="20"> Sutārakkho abhiyogo, kulārakkho vattaṃ bhave;</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="21">Vijjā hi kulaputtassa, nāyakassāpamādako.</gathalast>
